verbose_text: Interestingly, while the levels of key excitatory postsynaptic proteins including homer and PSD95 were unchanged, we observed a significant increase in the levels of the inhibitory GABA A R-beta2/3 subunits and the ASD associated neuroligin 3 adhesion molecule, which can be found at both inhibitory and excitatory postsynapses (XREF_FIG A).
